# Task workflow

Tasks live in `tasks/backlog/`, `tasks/active/`, `tasks/done/`. Every task file
uses the nine-section structure in `references/task-format.md` and is based on
`references/task-template.md`.

## Lifecycle

- **Backlog → Active**: move the file, start work, keep checkboxes current.
- **Active → Done**: when acceptance criteria are met, move to `tasks/done/`,
  add a completion date (`YYYY-MM-DD`) and a PR/commit reference, tick all boxes.

## Slicing

Keep each task small enough to ship and review on its own. If a slice stops
partial-but-correct, add a `## Maturity` section and follow the closure rule in
`references/task-maturity.md` (name a follow-up id or state none is owed).

## Validate

    python3 {{CHECKS_DIR}}/check_tasks.py --root . --strict

